value.value: The most primitive precursor in the granulocytic series, having fine, evenly distributed chromatin, several nucleoli, a high nuclear-to-cytoplasmic ration (5:1-7:1), and a nongranular basophilic cytoplasm. They reside in the bone marrow.

A hematopoietic multipotent progenitor cell is multipotent, but not capable of long-term self-renewal. These cells are characterized as lacking lineage cell surface markers and being CD34-positive in both mice and humans.

definition.value: Markers differ between mouse and human.

value.value: A progenitor cell restricted to the lymphoid lineage.

definition.value: Note that this is a class of cell types, not an identified single cell type.

value.value: A progenitor cell restricted to the myeloid lineage.

definition.value: Note that this is a class of cell types, not an identified single cell type.

value.value: A leukocyte with a single non-segmented nucleus in the mature form.
A neuron that releases serotonin as a neurotransmitter.

A monocyte that responds rapidly to microbial stimuli by secreting cytokines and antimicrobial factors and which is characterized by high expression of CCR2 in both rodents and humans, negative for the lineage markers CD3, CD19, and CD20, and of larger size than non-classical monocytes.

definition.value: Markers: CCR2+CXCCR1<low> (human, mouse, rat).

value.value: A macrophage which develops from an inflammatory monocyte and is recruited into the tissues in response to injury and infection as part of an inflammatory response. Markers include CD11b-positive, CD68-positive, and F4/80-positive.

definition.value: Markers: CD11b+, CD68+; Mouse: F4/80+; role or process: immune, inflammation (inflammatory response).

value.value: A macrophage that suppresses immune responses.

definition.value: Markers: May express: IL10, TGFbeta.

value.value: A macrophage constitutively resident in a particular tissue under non-inflammatory conditions, and capable of phagocytosing a variety of extracellular particulate material, including immune complexes, microorganisms, and dead cells.
A tissue-resident macrophage found in the central nervous system.

A border associated macrophage that is adjacent to a small blood vessel of a brain. A perivascular macrophage expresses the markers CD14, CD16 and CD163. In homeostatic conditions, this central nervous system macrophage has a non-motile cell body with extending and retracting projections through the blood vessel wall.
Cell committed to natural killer cell lineage that has the phenotype CD122-positive, CD34-positive, and CD117-positive. This cell type lacks expression of natural killer receptor proteins.

definition.value: These cells are also reportedly CD7-low, CD10-negative, CD45RA-positive, alpha-4-beta-7 integrin-high.

value.value: A lymphocyte of B lineage with the commitment to express an immunoglobulin complex.

definition.value: Types of B lineage lymphocytes include B cells and antibody secreting cells (plasmablasts and plasma cells).  Lymphocytes of B cell lineage can be distinguished from those of T cell lineage by their lack of CD3e (as part of the T cell receptor complex).

value.value: A cell of a hematopoietic lineage.
Conventional dendritic cell is a dendritic cell that is CD11c-high.

definition.value: Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:0000003)(PMID:19243617) These cells are also CD20-negative, MHCII-positive.

label.value: CD34-positive, CD38-positive common myeloid progenitor OR CD34-positive, CD38-positive common lymphoid progenitor

definition.value: Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:1100000)(PMID:19243617).

label.value: Kit and Sca1-positive hematopoietic stem cell

value.value: A hematopoietic stem cell that has plasma membrane part Kit-positive, SCA-1-positive, CD150-positive and CD34-negative.

definition.value: Cell markers are associated with mouse hematopoietic stem cell. Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:0000043)(PMID:19243617).

label.value: CD7-negative lymphoid progenitor OR granulocyte monocyte progenitor

definition.value: Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:1110000)(PMID:19243617).

label.value: CD115-positive monocyte OR common dendritic progenitor

definition.value: Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:1111000)(PMID:19243617).

value.value: A common lymphoid progenitor that is CD10-positive, CD45RA-positive, CD34-positive and CD38-positive.

definition.value: These markers are associated with human common lymphoid progenitors. Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:0000032)(PMID:19243617).

value.value: CD115-positive monocyte is a monocyte that is CD115-positive and CD11b-positive.

definition.value: These markers are associated with human cells. Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:0000033)(PMID:19243617).

value.value: CD133-positive hematopoietic stem cell is a hematopoietic stem cell that is CD34-positive, CD90-positive, and CD133-positive.

definition.value: Cell markers are associated with human hematopoietic stem cells. Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:0000035)(PMID:19243617).

value.value: A common myeloid progenitor that is CD34-positive, CD38-positive, IL3ra-low, CD10-negative, CD7-negative, CD45RA-negative, and IL-5Ralpha-negative.

definition.value: Markers are associated with human cell type. Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:0000038)(PMID:19243617).

value.value: CD7-negative lymphoid progenitor cell is a lymphoid progenitor cell that is CD34-positive, CD7-negative and CD45RA-negative.

definition.value: These markers are associated with human cells. Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:0000039)(PMID:19243617).

value.value: CD7-positive lymphoid progenitor cell is a lymphoid progenitor cell that is CD34-positive, CD7-positive and is CD45RA-negative.

definition.value: These markers are associated with human cells. Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:0000040)(PMID:19243617).

value.value: Common dendritic precursor is a hematopoietic progenitor cell that is CD117-low, CD135-positive, CD115-positive and lacks plasma membrane parts for hematopoietic lineage markers.

definition.value: Surface markers are for mouse cells. Originally described in the dendritic cell ontology (DC_CL:0000041) CDP are reportedly CD2-negative, CD3-negative, CD4-negative, CD5-negative, CD8a-negative, CD11c-positive, CD14-negative, CD19-negative, CD20-negative, CD56-negative, B220-negative, Ly6g-negative, MHCII-positive, and Ter119-negative. (PMID:19243617).

value.value: An excitatory granule cell with a soma located in the granular layer of cerebellar cortex. A mature cerebellar granule cell has short dendrites with a characteristic claw-like appearance and a long axon that ascends to the molecular layer where it bifurcates (except in non-teleost fish, where it does not bifurcate) and extends mediolaterally to form parallel fibers.

It has been noted in at least some mammalian species that granule cells are the most numerous cell type in the cerebellum and in the brain, with at least 99% of all cerebellar neurons being granule cells.
Granule cell that is part of the cerebral cortex.
Granule cell with a soma found in the hippocampus.
A connective tissue cell found in bone.
A monocyte that expresses CD14 and is negative for the lineage markers CD3, CD19, and CD20.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'monocyte'. Note that while CD14 is considered a reliable marker for human monocytes, it is only expressed on approximately 85% of mouse monocytes.

value.value: A progenitor cell committed to myeloid lineage, including the megakaryocyte and erythroid lineages. These cells are CD34-positive, and express Gata1, Gata2, C/EBPa, and Pu.1.

definition.value: CMP are reportedly CD16-positive, CD32-positive, CD38-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD110-negative, CD117-positive, CD123-positive, and SCA1-negative.

value.value: A hematopoietic oligopotent progenitor cell that has the ability to differentiate into limited cell types but lacks lineage cell markers and self renewal capabilities. Cell lacks hematopoeitic lineage markers.

A lymphocyte that lacks characteristic T cell, B cell, myeloid cell, and dendritic cell markers, that functions as part of the innate immune response to produce cytokines and other effector responses.
A progenitor cell committed to the erythroid lineage. This cell is ter119-positive but lacks expression of other hematopoietic lineage markers (lin-negative).
An innate lymphoid cell that is capable of producing the type 1 cytokine IFN-gamma, but not Th2 or Th17 cell-associated cytokines.
A lymphocyte of B lineage that is CD19-positive.

definition.value: Types of B lineage lymphocytes include B cells and antibody secreting cells (plasmablasts and plasma cells).  Lymphocytes of B cell lineage can be distinguished from those of T cell lineage by their lack of CD3e (as part of the T cell receptor complex).

value.value: A B cell that is CD19-positive.

An erythroid progenitor cell is Kit-positive, Ly6A-negative, CD41-negative, CD127-negative, and CD123-negative. This cell type is also described as being lin-negative, Kit-positive, CD150-negative, CD41-negative, CD105-positive, and FcgR-negative.

definition.value: Markers found on mouse cells.

value.value: A granulocyte monocyte progenitor is CD34-positive, CD38-positive, IL-3receptor-alpha-positive and is CD45RA-negative.

definition.value: Markers are for human cells. According to different research groups, CD45RA is present or absent on this cell population.

label.value: CD34-positive, CD38-positive megakaryocyte erythroid progenitor cell

value.value: A megakaryocyte erythroid progenitor cell is CD34-positive, CD38-positive and is IL3-receptor alpha-negative and CD45RA-negative.

definition.value: Markers are associated with human cell type.

label.value: Kit-positive, CD34-negative megakaryocyte erythroid progenitor cell

value.value: A megakaryocyte erythroid progenitor cell that is Kit-positive and is Sca1-negative, CD34-negative, CD90-negative, IL7r-alpha-negative and Fcgr II/III-low.

definition.value: Markers are associated with mouse cells.

value.value: A progenitor cell that can give rise to plasmacytoid and myeloid dendritic cells, and to monocytes and macrophages.
A lin-negative, MHC-II-negative, CD11c-positive, FLT3-positive cell with intermediate expression of SIRP-alpha.
A proerythoblast that is Kit-low, Lyg76-positive, and CD71-positive.

definition.value: Markers are associated with mouse cells.

value.value: A basophilic erythroblast that is Lyg 76-high and is Kit-negative.

definition.value: Cell surface markers are associated with mouse cells.

value.value: A polychromatophilic erythroblast that is Lyg 76-high and is Kit-negative.
An orthochromatophilic erythroblast that is ter119-high, CD71-low, and Kit-negative.

definition.value: Cell surface markers associated with mouse cells.

value.value: A reticulocyte that is Ly76-high and is Kit-negative.

definition.value: Marker associated with mouse cells.
